AI Stock Analyzer V2 — Complete Setup Guide

---

## Step 1: System Preparation

1. Update system:
   sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install required packages:
   sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv git curl -y

---

## Step 2: Create Project Folder

mkdir ~/stock-ai-agent
cd ~/stock-ai-agent

---

## Step 3: Create Virtual Environment

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# You should now see (venv) in terminal

---

## Step 4: Add Project Files

# Copy all project files (app/, templates/, static/, etc.)

# into this folder from your GitHub repo

---

## Step 5: Install Python Dependencies

pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

---

## Step 6: Install Ollama (Local AI)

curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

# Run model (downloads first time)

ollama run phi3

---

## Step 7: Get News API Key

1. Go to: https://newsapi.org
2. Click Sign Up
3. Login
4. Copy your API Key

---

## Step 8: Configure API Key

Create .env file:

nano .env

Add:

NEWS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

Save:
CTRL + X
Y
Enter

---

## Step 9: Protect API Key

nano .gitignore

Add:

.env
**pycache**/
*.pyc

---

## Step 10: Run Application

uvicorn app.main:app --reload

---

## Step 11: Open in Browser

http://127.0.0.1:8000

---

## Step 12: Test the App

Try inputs:

* TCS
* INFY
* AAPL

Click "Analyze"

---

## Common Issues & Fixes

1. Ollama not running:
   ollama run phi3

2. No news showing:

   * Check .env file
   * Verify API key

3. Slow performance:

   * Normal on 4GB system
   * Faster on 8GB+

4. Port already in use:
   uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8001

